y one to have actually followed through. "Ontology: Laying the Foundations" deals with "what is insofar as it is," and its four parts tackle traditional ontological assumptions and prejudices and traditional categories such as substance, thing, individual, whole, object, and phenomenon; a novel redefinition of existence and essence in terms of the ontological factors Dasein and Sosein and their interrelations; an analysis of modes of "givenness" and the ontological embeddedness of cognition in affective transcendent acts; and a discussion of the status of ideal being, including mathematical being, phenomenological essences, logical laws, values, and the interconnections between the ideal and real spheres. Hartmann’s work offers rich resources for those interested in overcoming the human-centeredness of much 20th century philosophy. Hartmann’s work offers rich resources for those interested in overcoming the human-centeredness of much 20th century philosophy.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 21. Jun 2021) 0aOntology. 0aReality. 4aNicolai Hartmann. 4aOntologie. 4aRealismus. 4aSein. 7aPHILOSOPHY / History & Surveys / Modern.2bisacsh  aBeing.  aNicolai Hartmann.  aOntology.  aRealism.1 aHartmann, Nicolai, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPeterson, Keith.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus eBook-Package 2019z978311071956708iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2019 Englishz978311061076508iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2019z9783110664232oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Philosophy 2019 Englishz978311061055008iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Philosophy 2019z9783110606423oZDB-23-DPH0 cEPUBz97831106247790 cprintz9